    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe undotree currently has quite a vintage look due to the ascii symbols used to represent the nodes and branches.\n\n<img width=\"369\" height=\"428\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6021fce6-452a-45a6-9f6f-c0f610c7be01\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nModern terminal emulators like [Ghostty](https://github.com/ghostty-org/ghostty/issues/2561) and [Kitty](https://github.com/kovidgoyal/kitty/pull/7681) support branch drawing characters (flog symbols) which can make the undotree much more aesthetically pleasing. Here's an **unfinished, incorrect** example of some experimenting with it:\n\n<img width=\"177\" height=\"425\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/951ac051-d1cb-44c4-8336-1de6298b01f9\" />\n\nIt would be great to either (1) detect if the character is supported (?) and use them automatically or (2) have an option to provide the character set to `undotree.open()`.\n\ncc @altermo\n\nAs a reference, here is a plugin that uses those characters but for showing Git branches: https://github.com/rbong/vim-flog",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
