            "body": "Hm not sure. The undotree is a tree, but it's a pretty weird one compared to other cases listed for the generic tree view.\n\nSince I saw your comment I've picked up the vim.ui.tree() implementation again, but I have no idea how we could reuse it to represent something similar to e.g. undo-line 61 from the image above. That is, 2 branches, one node that comes from branch 2, and another branch. Initial implementation should probably just look like netrw's file tree explorer, where each file (or directory) is on it's own line. ",
